		<h3>
			What's a Podcast? 
		</h3>
		<p>
			A podcast is an audio recording that can be delivered to an iPod or other types of mobile media players, which can then be listened to by a user whenever they want. Podcasts are typically saved in MP3 format so they can also be listened to on your computer. 
		</p>
		<h3>
			Podcasts on MAAP 
		</h3>
		<p>
			Mapping the African American Past is pleased to offer podcasts of all fifty-two locations in MAAP website. Listen to these recordings as you visit the selected places in New York city. The simplest way to subscribe to this podcast is to use iTunes. 
		</p>
		<p>
			<a title="Subscribe in iTunes" href="http://deimos3.apple.com/WebObjects/Core.woa/Browse/columbia.edu.2569373763.02609503921">
				<img style="border: 1px solid #ccc;" src="/static/images/icon_itunes_large.jpg" alt="iTunes" border="0" />
			</a>
		</p>
		<p>
			Once subscribed in iTunes, you can easily access any episode from the podcast feed, or move the podcast episodes to your mobile device. 
		</p>
		<p>
			You can also choose to listen to podcasts using a Web browser or other feed aggregators. 
		</p>
